com.iha.emulator.ui.simulations.performance

Class PerformanceSimulationPresenter

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.iha.emulator.ui.simulations.performance.PerformanceSimulationPresenter
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Presenter

    public class PerformanceSimulationPresenter
extends java.lang.Object
implements Presenter
    Class providing logic to user interactions for "Performance simulation". Part Presenter of MVP design pattern. Also serving main window of "Performance simulation"
    Author:
    Filip Sutovsky

        public void saveAll(javafx.collections.ObservableList<SimulationTask> tasks)
        Creates XML document for all given simulation tasks in list, that is saved to file chosen by invoked file save dialog. Uses separate Task. If given list is null, all created tasks are saved.
        Parameters:
        tasks - list of tasks to be saved, if null all created tasks are saved

      • checkMissingStopConditions

        private boolean checkMissingStopConditions()

        Returns:

      • switchCurrentTask

        public void switchCurrentTask(SimulationTask newTask)
        Selects given simulation task as current and displays it's information to user interface. If previous task is still running, it is stopped. If given simulation task is null, control buttons in navigation are disabled.
        Parameters:
        newTask - task to be set as current
